export class ServiceError extends Error {
  public readonly statusCode: number;

  constructor(statusCode: number, message: string) {
    super(message);
    this.name = "ServiceError";
    this.statusCode = statusCode;
  }
}
```

That is the entire file. No subclasses. The `statusCode` field carries 400 or 404 directly, matching the exact codes used today. Route handlers will `catch (e)` and check `e instanceof ServiceError` to decide what to send.

